        "text": "Based on the debug bundle summary and the handoff note, the issue appears to be:\n\n**Root Cause Analysis:**\n\n1. **Token prefix mismatch warning** - The debug bundle shows this as the trigger\n2. **Repeated auth retries without local token read** - The trace shows the agent keeps retrying auth without actually reading the local token file\n3. **Local token shows `[REDACTED_TOKEN]`** - This appears to be a demo/stale token\n\n**The Problem:**\nThe auth retry loop is firing because there's a **token prefix mismatch** between what's stored locally (`[REDACTED_TOKEN]`) and what the authentication system expects. The agent keeps retrying authentication but never re-reads the token file to get updated credentials, creating an infinite loop.\n\n**Immediate Fix:**\nThe local token (`~/.openclaw/token.txt`) contains `[REDACTED_TOKEN]` which appears to be a stale demo token. This needs to be updated with the correct production token that matches what the auth system expects.\n\n**Recommendation:**\n1. Replace the token in `~/.openclaw/token.txt` with the current valid token\n2. Ensure the agent re-reads the token file after auth failures instead of just retrying with the stale token\n3. Consider adding a mechanism to refresh/re-read local credentials when auth fails",
